'gnome-kiosk-script' is automatically invoked if one's gnome session (defined in
/var/lib/AccountsService/users/kiosk) is 'gnome-kiosk-script' rather than the usual 'ubuntu', and
the 'gnome-kiosk-script-session' package is installed. 'gnome-kiosk-script' is hardcoded to look in
~/.local/bin/gnome-kiosk-script, which we symlink to our actual script
/usr/local/bin/gnome-kiosk-script
